# Real .env files (git-ignored by this project's root .gitignore) hold
# secrets and per-environment values — never commit a real one. This
# .env.example documents what's needed, with a placeholder value, so a
# teammate cloning the repo knows exactly what to put in their own .env.
#
# The database name is the path segment right after the cluster host
# (here: "express") — MongoDB creates a database the first time
# something is actually written to it, so it doesn't need to exist
# ahead of time the way a Postgres schema does. This demo also uses its
# own dedicated collection name ("learning_tasks") inside that database,
# so it can never collide with any other collection already living there.
MONGODB_DATABASE_URL="mongodb+srv://user:password@cluster.mongodb.net/express"
